WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.251 --> 00:00:04.296
We need a stall to find my damn sister!

2
00:00:04.379 --> 00:00:07.174
Either she's managed to flee the city.
or she's very well-hidden.

3
00:00:07.257 --> 00:00:08.509
Is someone in your room?

4
00:00:08.592 --> 00:00:10.312
- [grunts. pants]
- Stop! [breathes shakily]

5
00:00:10.385 --> 00:00:11.595
[laughs]

6
00:00:11.678 --> 00:00:14.181
The bombs. We have to destroy them
before they can be used.

7
00:00:14.264 --> 00:00:17.976
I will go with Haniwa and Kofun.
We will free the children of Jerlamarel.

8
00:00:18.060 --> 00:00:20.646
[Harlan] The Military?
You think he's in league with Tormada?

9
00:00:20.729 --> 00:00:21.730
Come with me.

10
00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:24.525
I've been sneaking into Trivantes
since I was a boy.

11
00:00:24.608 --> 00:00:26.419
- You promised. Let me out of here!
- [Kofun shushes]

12
00:00:26.443 --> 00:00:29.655
I am not doing this for you.
I'm doing it for Wolffe.

13
00:00:30.155 --> 00:00:31.155
A gift for you.

14
00:00:32.156 --> 00:00:33.200
[sighs]

15
00:00:33.283 --> 00:00:35.053
[Maghra]
<i>The Witchfinders have grown too bold.</i>

16
00:00:35.077 --> 00:00:35.953
[grunting]

17
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:37.276
- [attacker] Witch!
- I got him!

18
00:00:37.329 --> 00:00:39.182
[Maghra]
<i>I want every last one of them arrested.</i>

19
00:00:39.206 --> 00:00:41.917
- [Tamacti Jun] <i>To what end?</i>
- [Maghra] <i>I am going to hang them.</i>

20
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:43.836
[grunting]

21
00:00:43.919 --> 00:00:45.838
[Maghra]
If you violate the royal edict again.

22
00:00:45.921 --> 00:00:49.174
you will suffer
far more than these men did today.

23
00:00:49.258 --> 00:00:50.258
[Baba Voss] Sibeth!

24
00:00:50.300 --> 00:00:52.100
- You freed her?
- Please just give him to me.

25
00:00:52.177 --> 00:00:54.471
- He is the child of prophecy.
- He can't see!

26
00:00:54.555 --> 00:00:55.764
- [grunts]
- [yelps]

27
00:00:55.848 --> 00:00:57.307
- [grunts]
- [screams]

28
00:00:57.391 --> 00:01:00.435
[Wolffe crying]

29
00:01:04.708 --> 00:01:08.003
- [people chattering]
- [Sibeth breathing heavily]

30
00:01:16.595 --> 00:01:18.430
[gasps. exhales sharply]

31
00:01:23.059 --> 00:01:24.352
[chuckles]

32
00:01:25.145 --> 00:01:26.396
[dog growls]

33
00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:34.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

34
00:01:36.781 --> 00:01:39.034
- [dog barking]
- [breathing shakily]

35
00:01:39.117 --> 00:01:40.410
[dog sniffing]

36
00:01:40.493 --> 00:01:41.661
[royal guard 1] Here we go.

37
00:01:41.745 --> 00:01:43.371
[breathing shakily continues]

38
00:01:44.456 --> 00:01:45.540
[horse whinnies]

39
00:01:55.759 --> 00:01:57.177
[royal guard 1] Got something.

40
00:01:57.260 --> 00:01:58.678
[barking continues. louder]

41
00:01:58.762 --> 00:01:59.763
Over here.

42
00:02:00.597 --> 00:02:02.641
[breathing shakily]

43
00:02:02.724 --> 00:02:03.725
[squelches]

44
00:02:03.808 --> 00:02:05.018
[royal guard 2] Check it out.

45
00:02:05.101 --> 00:02:06.518
[royal guard 1] Over this way.

46
00:02:08.855 --> 00:02:10.273
[royal guard 1] In the stables.

47
00:02:12.233 --> 00:02:14.319
[breathing heavily]

48
00:02:15.445 --> 00:02:18.281
[groans. gags]

49
00:02:19.032 --> 00:02:21.326
[dog barking. panting]

50
00:02:24.829 --> 00:02:28.375
[dog panting]

51
00:02:29.376 --> 00:02:32.462
[royal guard 1] Come on.
Nothing here but horses. Let's go.

52
00:02:33.296 --> 00:02:34.381
Let's check this out.

53
00:02:37.550 --> 00:02:39.386
Hey! Get outta here.

54
00:02:40.553 --> 00:02:42.430
Find someplace else to shit.

55
00:03:08.123 --> 00:03:09.374
[Pennsan] Coming through.

56
00:03:10.124 --> 00:03:11.375
[royal guard 3] Thank you. sir.

57
00:04:58.316 --> 00:05:00.110
[Baba Voss inhales sharply. sighs]

58
00:05:00.860 --> 00:05:03.113
- [breathes heavily]
- [panting]

59
00:05:03.196 --> 00:05:06.032
Listen. I have to go away
for a little while.

60
00:05:08.201 --> 00:05:10.453
And I know you would like to come with me.

61
00:05:10.537 --> 00:05:13.081
but you make too much noise.

62
00:05:14.124 --> 00:05:15.917
Even when I tell you to be quiet.

63
00:05:18.419 --> 00:05:21.756
Which makes it harder for me to kill
the people who I need to kill.

64
00:05:25.552 --> 00:05:26.761
But. most importantly…

65
00:05:28.555 --> 00:05:30.307
I need you to watch over this boy.

66
00:05:33.059 --> 00:05:36.730
He's my grandson. Wolffe.

67
00:05:40.191 --> 00:05:43.028
A boy named Wolffe and a dog named No.

68
00:05:45.113 --> 00:05:47.240
[chuckles. inhales sharply]

69
00:05:47.324 --> 00:05:49.784
I know you will protect him
and keep him safe.

70
00:05:50.619 --> 00:05:54.789
And if that evil mother of his tries
to take him again.

71
00:05:54.873 --> 00:05:57.292
you have my permission
to tear her throat out

72
00:05:57.375 --> 00:05:58.627
and eat her face.

73
00:05:59.878 --> 00:06:00.921
Okay?

74
00:06:04.132 --> 00:06:05.508
Good boy.

75
00:06:07.677 --> 00:06:10.013
[groans. sighs]

76
00:06:20.941 --> 00:06:22.692
[exhales deeply]

77
00:06:26.279 --> 00:06:28.365
[hawk cries]

78
00:06:30.825 --> 00:06:33.703
[Charlotte] I'm not saying I blame you.
I'm not one to blame.

79
00:06:34.204 --> 00:06:37.207
I'm just saying
I'm surprised you left Maghra alone

80
00:06:37.290 --> 00:06:39.417
when Sibeth's yet to be captured.

81
00:06:39.501 --> 00:06:41.962
[Baba Voss] Sibeth would be insane
to return to the palace.

82
00:06:42.045 --> 00:06:44.422
- [Charlotte] Sibeth is insane.
- [Baba Voss groans]

83
00:06:45.257 --> 00:06:46.675
[Wren. Haniwa chattering]

84
00:06:46.758 --> 00:06:49.928
I don't recognize this terrain.
Are you sure you're following the map?

85
00:06:50.011 --> 00:06:51.972
[sighs] I have to make
a stop along the way.

86
00:06:52.055 --> 00:06:54.349
[Charlotte smacks lips]
This is not along the way.

87
00:06:56.810 --> 00:06:58.561
[stutters] Dad.

88
00:06:59.479 --> 00:07:00.563
My son?

89
00:07:00.647 --> 00:07:02.065
[Kofun inhales deeply. sighs]

90
00:07:02.148 --> 00:07:03.316
I'm sorry.

91
00:07:04.484 --> 00:07:05.527
For what?

92
00:07:06.236 --> 00:07:09.281
I don't know what I was thinking.
I... [inhales deeply]

93
00:07:09.364 --> 00:07:10.824
I freed Sibeth.

94
00:07:11.616 --> 00:07:14.035
And. you know. she's gone.
and it's my fault.

95
00:07:15.036 --> 00:07:17.998
[Baba Voss inhales sharply. sighs]

96
00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:21.001
I have many things that I am sorry for.

97
00:07:21.835 --> 00:07:23.169
Many regrets.

98
00:07:24.296 --> 00:07:27.007
But I never regret anything
that I did for my children.

99
00:07:28.466 --> 00:07:29.467
Okay?

100
00:07:30.260 --> 00:07:32.012
When you were freeing Sibeth.

101
00:07:32.095 --> 00:07:34.472
you were thinking like a father.
not a traitor.

102
00:07:34.556 --> 00:07:36.266
You were doing it for your son.

103
00:07:36.766 --> 00:07:38.560
Don't ever apologize about that.

104
00:07:40.353 --> 00:07:41.396
Thank you.

105
00:07:43.315 --> 00:07:44.441
How is your back?

106
00:07:45.025 --> 00:07:47.986
[exhales deeply]
Um. it hurts when I breathe. [chuckles]

107
00:07:48.069 --> 00:07:50.864
Yes. That pain is good.

108
00:07:50.947 --> 00:07:52.574
It reminds us that we're still alive.

109
00:07:52.657 --> 00:07:54.159
- [Kofun] Yeah.
- [Baba Voss] Yes.

110
00:07:54.242 --> 00:07:56.244
- [groans]
- [Baba Voss] Stay alive. my boy.

111
00:07:56.328 --> 00:07:59.497
- [Kofun splutters. sighs]
- [Baba Voss groans. chuckles]

112
00:08:04.711 --> 00:08:06.796
[Harlan]
From the moment Sibeth arrived in Pennsa.

113
00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:08.256
I knew she was gonna be a problem.

114
00:08:08.340 --> 00:08:11.760
I just didn't realize
quite how much of a problem.

115
00:08:14.054 --> 00:08:16.681
I'd like to think
I would've been more decisive.

116
00:08:17.557 --> 00:08:21.311
- Maybe had her killed in her sleep.
- [chuckles]

117
00:08:22.312 --> 00:08:23.939
So. instead. you married Maghra.

118
00:08:25.315 --> 00:08:26.358
Yeah.

119
00:08:26.983 --> 00:08:29.778
Seemed the best way
to keep a seat at my own table.

120
00:08:29.861 --> 00:08:31.363
And how has that worked out?

121
00:08:33.823 --> 00:08:35.033
Has its moments.

122
00:08:36.826 --> 00:08:38.078
And does Maghra know?

123
00:08:39.287 --> 00:08:40.288
Know what?

124
00:08:40.372 --> 00:08:41.873
That you're in love with her.

125
00:08:44.501 --> 00:08:45.669
[chuckles]

126
00:08:47.337 --> 00:08:49.714
I suppose she'd have to be a fool
not to know.

127
00:08:52.425 --> 00:08:55.025
Well. I think she's a fool for knowing
and doing nothing about it.

128
00:08:55.637 --> 00:08:56.972
She's a married fool.

129
00:08:57.764 --> 00:09:00.016
- And that's what I tell myself about you.
- Ha!

130
00:09:02.227 --> 00:09:04.688
At least I get you into my bed
now and then. [sighs]

131
00:09:04.771 --> 00:09:07.232
I imagine you're not as lucky
with your queen.

132
00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:18.243
[Guntar whistles] Whoa.

133
00:09:18.326 --> 00:09:19.553
- Who's there?
- [soldiers grunt]

134
00:09:19.577 --> 00:09:21.871
- Calm your men. They're with me.
- Stand down.

135
00:09:22.372 --> 00:09:23.415
Guntar!

136
00:09:23.498 --> 00:09:24.541
Yeah.

137
00:09:26.126 --> 00:09:28.628
Well. this is where I leave you.

138
00:09:29.212 --> 00:09:30.839
- [grunts]
- What? Where are you going?

139
00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:34.050
Guntar and Pelz are associates of mine.

140
00:09:34.718 --> 00:09:36.677
I'm gonna travel the rest
of the way together.

141
00:09:36.761 --> 00:09:38.220
then I'll meet you at your house.

142
00:09:38.305 --> 00:09:41.057
I can give you knots
and call you a diplomatic emissary.

143
00:09:41.141 --> 00:09:44.561
No. we know other. quieter ways in.

144
00:09:45.186 --> 00:09:47.022
It's better for all concerned.

145
00:09:47.105 --> 00:09:49.316
- You don't trust me.
- Course not.

146
00:09:50.317 --> 00:09:51.818
That's what I like about you.

147
00:09:55.196 --> 00:09:56.197
[chuckles]

148
00:09:59.576 --> 00:10:01.995
[laughs] Yes.

149
00:10:02.078 --> 00:10:03.413
[fingers snapping]

150
00:10:03.496 --> 00:10:06.291
Come here. My brother.

151
00:10:06.374 --> 00:10:07.667
[laughs]

152
00:10:25.435 --> 00:10:26.811
[Kofun] What happened here?

153
00:10:27.437 --> 00:10:30.106
[Baba Voss] This is where we were attacked
by Tormada's bombs.

154
00:10:33.318 --> 00:10:35.111
It's like the earth was torn apart.

155
00:10:36.279 --> 00:10:37.489
[Kofun sighs]

156
00:10:38.281 --> 00:10:40.033
This is where Bow Lion was killed.

157
00:10:43.453 --> 00:10:45.830
[inhales deeply. sighs]

158
00:10:46.790 --> 00:10:48.667
This is a weapon of the ancestors.

159
00:10:48.750 --> 00:10:52.128
Built by the Trivantian army.
They are called bombs.

160
00:10:52.212 --> 00:10:54.339
[Ranger] I felt the earth come apart.

161
00:10:54.422 --> 00:10:57.008
If the Trivantians have weapons
that can do this.

162
00:10:57.092 --> 00:10:58.760
no one will be able to stop them.

163
00:10:59.261 --> 00:11:02.389
We know where the bombs are.
We are on our way to destroy them now.

164
00:11:02.472 --> 00:11:04.392
[Lu] And you've come here
to drag Ranger into it.

165
00:11:04.474 --> 00:11:07.102
Haven't you done enough to us.
Baba Voss? [sighs]

166
00:11:07.185 --> 00:11:09.354
You fled Trivantes just as I did.

167
00:11:09.437 --> 00:11:11.982
And when they invade.
you will find yourself back in there.

168
00:11:12.065 --> 00:11:14.901
Mmm. maybe. Maybe not.

169
00:11:14.985 --> 00:11:16.987
There's no coal in these mountains.

170
00:11:17.070 --> 00:11:19.614
No fruit. Just the wolves and us.

171
00:11:19.698 --> 00:11:21.574
And they have always left us alone.

172
00:11:21.658 --> 00:11:23.159
Who cares who rules below?

173
00:11:23.243 --> 00:11:25.537
- You say that now.
- [Lu] I say it always.

174
00:11:26.413 --> 00:11:29.416
We belong to no nation.
And we will fight for no nation.

175
00:11:29.499 --> 00:11:32.836
Baba. you know I have no love
for the Trivantians.

176
00:11:33.336 --> 00:11:35.380
But I have no reason to fight for Paya.

177
00:11:35.463 --> 00:11:37.340
[breathes heavily]

178
00:11:37.424 --> 00:11:38.883
I will give you one. then.

179
00:11:39.926 --> 00:11:41.052
Tormada.

180
00:11:47.976 --> 00:11:48.977
Shut up.

181
00:11:49.603 --> 00:11:53.273
Does it really surprise you
to know that he wields this weapon?

182
00:11:53.356 --> 00:11:54.774
Fuck you. Baba Voss.

183
00:11:58.069 --> 00:12:00.071
[Ranger sighs]

184
00:12:13.793 --> 00:12:14.878
He'll come.

185
00:12:14.961 --> 00:12:16.254
[Haniwa chuckles]

186
00:12:24.804 --> 00:12:26.723
[people chattering]

187
00:12:30.852 --> 00:12:32.604
[chickens squawking]

188
00:12:37.484 --> 00:12:39.486
[squawking continues]

189
00:12:56.211 --> 00:12:57.712
Did it have to be chickens?

190
00:12:57.796 --> 00:13:00.382
[chuckles] Chicken shit does
throw the dogs off.

191
00:13:00.465 --> 00:13:02.384
Yeah. it throws me off a little too.

192
00:13:02.467 --> 00:13:04.552
Well. you didn't give me
very much time to plan.

193
00:13:05.804 --> 00:13:07.097
Fair enough.

194
00:13:07.180 --> 00:13:08.598
[Guntar] All right. listen.

195
00:13:08.682 --> 00:13:11.309
We're gonna be waiting
for you at the usual place.

196
00:13:11.393 --> 00:13:13.061
Come and find me when it's time to leave.

197
00:13:13.144 --> 00:13:15.188
Fine. What are you doing now?

198
00:13:15.272 --> 00:13:18.441
Well… [smacks lips] …I guess
I'll have to sell these fucking chickens.

199
00:13:18.525 --> 00:13:19.651
[both chuckle]

200
00:13:30.203 --> 00:13:32.080
[Sibeth] Ah. ah. ah!

201
00:13:36.668 --> 00:13:39.421
[breathing heavily]

202
00:13:45.302 --> 00:13:48.263
[sighs]

203
00:14:00.984 --> 00:14:01.985
[coughs]

204
00:14:02.068 --> 00:14:04.779
[gags. gasps]

205
00:14:04.863 --> 00:14:07.365
[coughing]

206
00:14:08.908 --> 00:14:10.201
[gasps]

207
00:14:10.285 --> 00:14:11.286
[grunts]

208
00:14:11.369 --> 00:14:13.788
[insects skittering]

209
00:14:29.387 --> 00:14:31.806
[breathing heavily]

210
00:14:41.232 --> 00:14:43.193
[coughs. sniffs]

211
00:14:43.276 --> 00:14:45.278
Mmm! [sniffs]

212
00:14:45.362 --> 00:14:47.989
[humming]

213
00:14:48.073 --> 00:14:51.451
[wolves howling]

214
00:14:54.579 --> 00:14:56.581
[howling continues]

215
00:14:57.415 --> 00:14:59.793
[sighs] You smell like a farm.

216
00:15:01.503 --> 00:15:04.589
I'm painfully aware. Thank you.

217
00:15:06.633 --> 00:15:10.512
So… [sighs] …tell me about the Bank.

218
00:15:11.388 --> 00:15:12.472
Her name is Nevla.

219
00:15:13.390 --> 00:15:15.725
She's a politician but also a patriot.

220
00:15:16.643 --> 00:15:19.203
If there's a rogue faction
in the government. she'll root it out.

221
00:15:20.647 --> 00:15:21.815
If she believes you.

222
00:15:22.732 --> 00:15:25.694
If she doesn't.
this will be a very short conversation.

223
00:15:25.777 --> 00:15:27.028
- [breathes deeply]
- [chuckles]

224
00:15:27.112 --> 00:15:28.113
[staff tapping]

225
00:15:33.451 --> 00:15:36.037
Announcing the High Councillor. the Bank.

226
00:15:36.788 --> 00:15:37.789
Councillor.

227
00:15:37.872 --> 00:15:39.165
Roscoe. wait outside.

228
00:15:40.458 --> 00:15:41.668
Ambassador Trovere.

229
00:15:42.252 --> 00:15:45.171
I assume you have the former queen
tucked away somewhere.

230
00:15:45.255 --> 00:15:47.382
[exhales deeply]
There's been a bit of a wrinkle.

231
00:15:48.300 --> 00:15:49.485
- A wrinkle?
- [inhales sharply]

232
00:15:49.509 --> 00:15:51.052
She brought me instead.

233
00:15:51.886 --> 00:15:52.887
[sniffs]

234
00:15:53.388 --> 00:15:54.472
And who are you?

235
00:15:56.016 --> 00:15:57.225
I'm Harlan.

236
00:15:57.726 --> 00:16:00.687
Lord of Pennsa.
husband to Queen Maghra of Paya.

237
00:16:01.313 --> 00:16:02.564
Have you lost your mind?

238
00:16:02.647 --> 00:16:05.567
I assure you.
you'll want to hear what he has to say.

239
00:16:05.650 --> 00:16:06.943
Everything depends on it.

240
00:16:08.486 --> 00:16:10.697
[the Bank inhales deeply] Lord Harlan.

241
00:16:11.281 --> 00:16:13.408
Your reputation precedes you.

242
00:16:14.284 --> 00:16:16.953
Oh. that's unfortunate.

243
00:16:18.330 --> 00:16:20.498
But I assure you. I am here to help.

244
00:16:22.459 --> 00:16:23.460
You see…

245
00:16:24.586 --> 00:16:28.381
a rogue faction of your army is set
to march on Pennsa

246
00:16:28.465 --> 00:16:31.968
with advanced weapons
developed by a scientist named Tormada.

247
00:16:33.219 --> 00:16:38.224
Now. these weapons have the power
to flatten buildings. cities even.

248
00:16:39.225 --> 00:16:40.894
And. yes. they will attack us first.

249
00:16:40.977 --> 00:16:43.939
But make no mistake.
this is a coup against your government.

250
00:16:45.065 --> 00:16:46.149
You're insane.

251
00:16:46.900 --> 00:16:49.319
- That's… beside the point...
- Harlan.

252
00:16:50.362 --> 00:16:51.613
He is not lying.

253
00:16:53.823 --> 00:16:57.911
[inhales deeply] The last Payan queen
accused us of drowning an entire city.

254
00:16:57.994 --> 00:17:00.080
Now this Payan queen accuses us

255
00:17:00.163 --> 00:17:02.540
of a sneak attack
with some fantastical weapon.

256
00:17:02.624 --> 00:17:05.418
Now. let's be clear.
I'm not accusing your government.

257
00:17:06.461 --> 00:17:09.923
Although. it's likely your buddy.
the Military. is involved somewhere.

258
00:17:10.006 --> 00:17:11.800
You need to stop talking.

259
00:17:11.883 --> 00:17:13.718
He needs to stop talking now.

260
00:17:14.386 --> 00:17:15.470
Trovere. a word.

261
00:17:29.484 --> 00:17:30.902
[clicks tongue]

262
00:17:40.954 --> 00:17:42.372
[yawns]

263
00:17:42.455 --> 00:17:45.417
[whistling]

264
00:18:07.022 --> 00:18:08.231
[exhales heavily]

265
00:18:14.862 --> 00:18:16.239
[sighs deeply]

266
00:18:17.032 --> 00:18:19.159
[staff tapping. approaching]

267
00:18:19.242 --> 00:18:20.284
[sighs]

268
00:18:20.368 --> 00:18:22.704
[Trovere]
My God. Harlan. Have you no fear at all?

269
00:18:22.787 --> 00:18:23.788
Oh. come on.

270
00:18:24.539 --> 00:18:26.582
She was either gonna believe us or not.

271
00:18:26.666 --> 00:18:28.208
She doesn't believe us.

272
00:18:29.419 --> 00:18:30.837
[sighs]

273
00:18:30.921 --> 00:18:34.257
But she doesn't not believe us. [sighs]

274
00:18:35.967 --> 00:18:37.886
She clearly senses something is amiss.

275
00:18:38.762 --> 00:18:39.804
[Harlan] Really?

276
00:18:41.348 --> 00:18:43.475
She told me
Tormada is actually in the city.

277
00:18:45.685 --> 00:18:48.188
He is scheduled
to address the Triangle tomorrow.

278
00:18:48.271 --> 00:18:49.356
Interesting.

279
00:18:50.815 --> 00:18:51.942
So. what do we do?

280
00:18:52.025 --> 00:18:53.109
We do nothing.

281
00:18:55.320 --> 00:18:56.529
We make ourselves scarce.

282
00:18:56.613 --> 00:18:58.782
[breathes shakily]

283
00:19:00.742 --> 00:19:03.244
Nevla knows a military scientist
couldn't command the army

284
00:19:03.328 --> 00:19:05.455
without help from someone higher up.

285
00:19:05.538 --> 00:19:08.333
[inhales deeply]
She will quietly investigate. [sighs]

286
00:19:10.752 --> 00:19:12.754
In the meantime.
no one can know I've returned.

287
00:19:12.837 --> 00:19:15.423
or Sibeth's absence will become a problem.

288
00:19:15.507 --> 00:19:16.591
Understood.

289
00:19:18.969 --> 00:19:20.637
So…

290
00:19:24.432 --> 00:19:25.433
dinner?

291
00:19:29.938 --> 00:19:31.940
[howling]

292
00:19:32.774 --> 00:19:35.068
[all howling]

293
00:19:45.036 --> 00:19:47.581
[howling continues]

294
00:19:50.834 --> 00:19:52.877
[breathing shakily]

295
00:20:01.469 --> 00:20:04.389
You're gonna make it very hard
for me to leave.

296
00:20:06.558 --> 00:20:07.809
[Trovere inhales deeply]

297
00:20:09.102 --> 00:20:10.395
What if you just didn't?

298
00:20:10.937 --> 00:20:12.647
[chuckles] Didn't what?

299
00:20:13.898 --> 00:20:15.025
[inhales deeply]

300
00:20:15.984 --> 00:20:18.528
What is really waiting for you
back in Pennsa?

301
00:20:20.363 --> 00:20:23.033
- [chuckles]
- [sighs]

302
00:20:23.116 --> 00:20:25.994
I have devoted my whole life
to building that city.

303
00:20:28.622 --> 00:20:31.041
And the queen took it from you overnight.

304
00:20:33.543 --> 00:20:35.420
Now you're a guest in your own house.

305
00:20:36.004 --> 00:20:37.672
In a marriage of convenience.

306
00:20:37.756 --> 00:20:40.008
None of which suits a man
of your independent nature.

307
00:20:40.091 --> 00:20:41.384
if I'm being honest.

308
00:20:46.681 --> 00:20:47.849
[breathes heavily]

309
00:20:50.977 --> 00:20:52.228
Leave it behind you.

310
00:20:53.897 --> 00:20:56.858
[sighs] We can have
a wonderful life together here.

311
00:20:56.942 --> 00:20:59.611
You can... You can build something new.

312
00:21:00.946 --> 00:21:04.866
[sighs]
Trivantes has much more to offer you.

313
00:21:07.285 --> 00:21:08.536
And so do I.

314
00:21:09.162 --> 00:21:10.538
[inhales sharply]

315
00:21:19.464 --> 00:21:22.425
It's a very appealing offer. [sighs]

316
00:21:23.677 --> 00:21:25.178
[Trovere sighs]

317
00:21:25.262 --> 00:21:26.763
But not one you can accept.

318
00:21:29.057 --> 00:21:30.267
It's my city.

319
00:21:32.018 --> 00:21:34.854
[inhales sharply]
Are you sure this is about Pennsa?

320
00:21:38.608 --> 00:21:41.528
Yeah. What else?

321
00:21:43.571 --> 00:21:45.365
[sighs. groans]

322
00:21:45.448 --> 00:21:47.367
She will never love you. Harlan.

323
00:21:47.450 --> 00:21:49.452
[sighs]

324
00:21:52.414 --> 00:21:53.540
And yet…

325
00:21:55.542 --> 00:21:57.752
I can't bring myself to desert her.

326
00:22:02.882 --> 00:22:04.634
You're better than she deserves.

327
00:22:07.053 --> 00:22:08.805
You're better than I deserve.

328
00:22:11.850 --> 00:22:13.768
And still. we both end up alone.

329
00:22:16.980 --> 00:22:18.982
[Ranger]
Both of your children are sighted.

330
00:22:20.191 --> 00:22:23.361
They're lucky you took them in
and protected them as you did.

331
00:22:24.654 --> 00:22:27.091
[Baba Voss] Sometimes I think
they would've been better served

332
00:22:27.115 --> 00:22:29.117
if I had taken their sight as babies.

333
00:22:29.826 --> 00:22:32.287
[Ranger]
We'll never know. so no use wondering.

334
00:22:33.288 --> 00:22:34.539
[chuckles]

335
00:22:36.374 --> 00:22:40.587
When you were up on the mountain with me.
your heart was here with them.

336
00:22:41.212 --> 00:22:43.840
Now you're with them.
but your tread is no lighter.

337
00:22:45.050 --> 00:22:46.301
What will it take?

338
00:22:47.177 --> 00:22:50.347
Well. ask again when we've destroyed
those weapons. my friend.

339
00:22:51.222 --> 00:22:53.767
The weapons built by Edo's people.

340
00:22:53.850 --> 00:22:55.685
So you still blame yourself.

341
00:22:57.187 --> 00:22:59.940
You and I come from the same place.

342
00:23:00.523 --> 00:23:02.400
We have enough to atone for as it is.

343
00:23:02.484 --> 00:23:06.404
Taking on the sins of others
is just greedy. if you ask me.

344
00:23:07.739 --> 00:23:09.991
But if you want to feel guilt
about something.

345
00:23:11.284 --> 00:23:14.245
feel guilty about dragging me
from the comfort of my home

346
00:23:14.329 --> 00:23:15.830
to go on this endless walk.

347
00:23:15.914 --> 00:23:17.916
- [laughs]
- [sighs]

348
00:23:19.709 --> 00:23:22.587
[Tormada] If you think about it.
it's a beautiful process.

349
00:23:23.171 --> 00:23:25.173
We dig the coal out of the earth.

350
00:23:26.174 --> 00:23:27.842
we heat it to the same temperature

351
00:23:27.926 --> 00:23:30.053
at which it was forged
in the earth's core.

352
00:23:30.845 --> 00:23:35.141
And that same fantastic. unimaginable heat

353
00:23:35.225 --> 00:23:39.437
that once formed it
in the molten depths of our planet

354
00:23:40.146 --> 00:23:43.441
now causes its immediate deterioration.

355
00:23:44.025 --> 00:23:46.653
And with that deterioration.
we find the true prize.

356
00:23:46.736 --> 00:23:51.908
We release the energy it's been storing.
like a hidden treasure.

357
00:23:51.992 --> 00:23:53.410
since it was formed.

358
00:23:53.493 --> 00:23:58.039
It's as though we were stealing
the very power of creation itself

359
00:23:58.123 --> 00:23:59.874
from inside the Earth.

360
00:23:59.958 --> 00:24:02.377
And then. of course.
we use that power as a weapon.

361
00:24:02.460 --> 00:24:06.715
One that can obliterate our enemies
in a matter of seconds.

362
00:24:06.798 --> 00:24:08.091
[murmuring]

363
00:24:08.174 --> 00:24:12.262
Which may sound like a nasty. unworthy use

364
00:24:12.345 --> 00:24:15.348
of such a magnificent feat
of nature and science.

365
00:24:15.432 --> 00:24:17.350
but when you consider the alternative.

366
00:24:17.434 --> 00:24:20.729
the battlefields of bloody combat.

367
00:24:20.812 --> 00:24:24.316
the vulgar stabbing and clubbing of war.

368
00:24:25.817 --> 00:24:28.361
it's quite an elegant solution. I think.

369
00:24:29.070 --> 00:24:32.782
Our victory was fast and decisive.

370
00:24:34.034 --> 00:24:36.161
Only a handful of our soldiers fell.

371
00:24:36.244 --> 00:24:41.166
while we decimated their entire army
in a matter of minutes.

372
00:24:41.666 --> 00:24:43.793
- Their entire army?
- [Tormada] Mmm.

373
00:24:43.877 --> 00:24:45.587
You are exaggerating. of course.

374
00:24:45.670 --> 00:24:47.130
No. he is not.

375
00:24:47.881 --> 00:24:50.926
Dispatches from the western front
say the same thing.

376
00:24:51.009 --> 00:24:54.471
Total annihilation in a matter of moments.

377
00:24:54.554 --> 00:24:58.016
That's very impressive.
How many of these weapons have you built?

378
00:24:58.808 --> 00:25:01.061
[Tormada] Almost 200. and more every day.

379
00:25:02.187 --> 00:25:06.066
Now is the time to act.
quickly and decisively.

380
00:25:06.149 --> 00:25:07.734
and unleash them on our enemies.

381
00:25:07.817 --> 00:25:09.861
Which enemies do you mean?

382
00:25:09.945 --> 00:25:13.490
Well. Paya for starters.

383
00:25:13.573 --> 00:25:16.034
What Tormada means to say is

384
00:25:16.117 --> 00:25:19.913
the mere demonstration
of these new weapons

385
00:25:19.996 --> 00:25:24.751
will allow us to change the dynamic
of our negotiations for the better.

386
00:25:24.834 --> 00:25:26.378
[Tormada] No. Councillor.

387
00:25:26.920 --> 00:25:32.425
What I mean to say is that my bombs
will allow us to conquer their kingdom

388
00:25:32.509 --> 00:25:34.177
and claim it as our own.

389
00:25:34.261 --> 00:25:36.179
Your bombs?

390
00:25:36.263 --> 00:25:37.097
[murmuring]

391
00:25:37.180 --> 00:25:39.474
You have forgotten your place. Tormada.

392
00:25:40.433 --> 00:25:43.228
They are not your weapons.
They belong to the republic.

393
00:25:43.311 --> 00:25:48.775
And how. and if. they are used
will be decided by this council!

394
00:25:48.858 --> 00:25:52.862
Hmm. Agree to disagree. Councillor.

395
00:25:54.155 --> 00:25:56.491
They are. in fact. my bombs.

396
00:25:56.574 --> 00:25:58.618
They are under my control. are they not?

397
00:25:59.369 --> 00:26:02.956
And as a decorated general
such as yourself would know.

398
00:26:03.623 --> 00:26:06.918
whoever controls the weapons owns the day.

399
00:26:07.002 --> 00:26:07.836
[murmuring]

400
00:26:07.919 --> 00:26:09.546
You insubordinate bastard!

401
00:26:09.629 --> 00:26:11.923
- Tormada is right.
- What?

402
00:26:12.007 --> 00:26:14.342
Our empire grows weaker by the day

403
00:26:14.426 --> 00:26:17.304
because this council seeks
to appease our enemies

404
00:26:17.387 --> 00:26:18.805
instead of defeating them.

405
00:26:18.888 --> 00:26:20.432
What are you saying. Councillor?

406
00:26:20.515 --> 00:26:23.226
I'm saying this council has lost its way.

407
00:26:23.310 --> 00:26:26.855
Someone needs to give Trivantes
the leadership it deserves.

408
00:26:26.938 --> 00:26:31.901
Careful. Nevla.
Your words border on treason.

409
00:26:31.985 --> 00:26:35.238
Well. then. let's have no more words.

410
00:26:35.322 --> 00:26:37.466
- [clamoring]
- [the Military] Nevla. what are you doing?

411
00:26:37.490 --> 00:26:39.159
- Don't do this!
- [fuse hissing]

412
00:26:39.242 --> 00:26:41.244
[clamoring continues]

413
00:26:47.500 --> 00:26:49.920
- Trovere?
- [panting]

414
00:26:50.003 --> 00:26:53.423
- We have to go. Now!
- W... Wait. what's happening?

415
00:26:53.506 --> 00:26:56.009
We can't be here. Hurry!

416
00:26:56.551 --> 00:27:00.180
Well. no.
Will you just tell me what's going on...

417
00:27:01.765 --> 00:27:03.600
[debris crashing]

418
00:27:03.683 --> 00:27:06.853
[people of the Triangle screaming. crying]

419
00:27:13.109 --> 00:27:16.488
[leaves rustling]

420
00:27:48.144 --> 00:27:49.145
[twig snaps]

421
00:27:52.774 --> 00:27:54.025
[leaves rustle]

422
00:28:04.035 --> 00:28:05.662
[rabbit nibbling]

423
00:28:15.297 --> 00:28:16.297
[grunts]

424
00:28:19.175 --> 00:28:20.885
No. [pants]

425
00:28:22.012 --> 00:28:24.055
[whimpering]

426
00:28:28.476 --> 00:28:32.188
- [wails]
- [thunderclap]

427
00:28:34.482 --> 00:28:39.446
[inhales deeply. wails]

428
00:28:52.167 --> 00:28:53.627
[Harlan] Mmm.

429
00:28:57.380 --> 00:28:58.632
[grunts]

430
00:29:01.301 --> 00:29:03.803
- [groans]
- [Trovere] You're okay. Just relax.

431
00:29:04.804 --> 00:29:06.640
[sighs] You've had quite a shock.

432
00:29:09.267 --> 00:29:10.435
What was that?

433
00:29:12.228 --> 00:29:13.605
It was Tormada's weapon.

434
00:29:16.358 --> 00:29:17.776
He destroyed the Triangle.

435
00:29:20.695 --> 00:29:21.696
What?

436
00:29:25.200 --> 00:29:27.327
He killed the entire council?

437
00:29:27.410 --> 00:29:28.411
Not all.

438
00:29:29.955 --> 00:29:31.081
Not the Bank.

439
00:29:31.581 --> 00:29:32.624
Nevla.

440
00:29:36.711 --> 00:29:37.921
She was a part of it.

441
00:29:40.840 --> 00:29:41.883
[Trovere] Yes.

442
00:29:49.933 --> 00:29:51.434
And so are you.

443
00:29:55.105 --> 00:29:57.816
Tormada. Nevla…

444
00:30:00.193 --> 00:30:01.236
and you.

445
00:30:01.861 --> 00:30:04.322
The third side of the Triangle.

446
00:30:05.198 --> 00:30:06.908
I was given no choice.

447
00:30:08.785 --> 00:30:10.829
This has been planned
ever since Greenhill Gap.

448
00:30:10.912 --> 00:30:12.330
The Triangle was corrupted.

449
00:30:12.414 --> 00:30:14.833
Nevla and Tormada approached me
to replace the People.

450
00:30:14.916 --> 00:30:17.961
- There was no saying no to them.
- Fine. Fine.

451
00:30:20.755 --> 00:30:23.300
But what am I doing here? Huh?

452
00:30:25.510 --> 00:30:30.140
What role do I play
in this little revolution of yours?

453
00:30:31.600 --> 00:30:33.602
I couldn't leave you in Pennsa to die.

454
00:30:35.353 --> 00:30:36.771
[Harlan scoffs]

455
00:30:36.855 --> 00:30:38.189
Are you serious?

456
00:30:44.154 --> 00:30:47.324
You've just witnessed the power
of these bombs.

457
00:30:48.074 --> 00:30:50.452
These weapons change everything.

458
00:30:50.535 --> 00:30:51.661
Paya is finished.

459
00:30:52.621 --> 00:30:54.080
Why die for it?

460
00:30:54.164 --> 00:30:55.874
Before your queen. who loves another.

461
00:30:55.957 --> 00:30:58.793
when you could live
at the top of the new order? [sobs]

462
00:30:58.877 --> 00:31:02.088
[breathes shakily. sighs deeply]

463
00:31:02.881 --> 00:31:03.965
[kisses]

464
00:31:04.049 --> 00:31:05.133
I love you.

465
00:31:06.593 --> 00:31:09.054
Oh. I've risked everything
to save you. [kisses]

466
00:31:11.306 --> 00:31:12.933
I'm sorry it had to be done this way.

467
00:31:13.016 --> 00:31:15.644
but… [inhales deeply]
…now you have to choose.

468
00:31:18.605 --> 00:31:19.606
Choose?

469
00:31:22.359 --> 00:31:23.360
What?

470
00:31:24.361 --> 00:31:28.573
You or… prison?

471
00:31:30.533 --> 00:31:32.077
- Death. what?
- [sighs]

472
00:31:32.160 --> 00:31:33.954
No. of course not. [inhales deeply]

473
00:31:34.037 --> 00:31:35.497
If you want to go back to Pennsa.

474
00:31:35.580 --> 00:31:37.749
I will grieve for you.
but I won't stop you.

475
00:31:41.836 --> 00:31:45.799
[sighing]

476
00:31:49.803 --> 00:31:51.888
You've always been a survivor. Harlan.

477
00:31:52.931 --> 00:31:54.224
It's time to survive.

478
00:32:01.398 --> 00:32:03.483
[thunderclap]

479
00:32:08.405 --> 00:32:10.615
[panting. grunting]

480
00:32:27.507 --> 00:32:30.385
[panting. grunting]

481
00:32:46.401 --> 00:32:48.653
[Tamacti Jun]
It's warmer inside the palace. you know.

482
00:32:50.322 --> 00:32:51.740
Where do you think she is?

483
00:32:52.490 --> 00:32:53.908
[Tamacti Jun] I don't know.

484
00:32:55.994 --> 00:32:58.914
Three times now. I've tried to kill her.

485
00:33:00.206 --> 00:33:02.083
And each time she deserved it more.

486
00:33:02.167 --> 00:33:05.462
And yet. as I sit here
and listen to this storm.

487
00:33:05.545 --> 00:33:09.299
I find myself wondering
if she is warm and dry.

488
00:33:10.634 --> 00:33:15.722
[Tamacti Jun] Your sister has a unique way
of getting inside peoples' souls.

489
00:33:18.350 --> 00:33:19.643
You think we'll find her?

490
00:33:20.602 --> 00:33:22.896
After this storm.
our dogs will be useless.

491
00:33:24.564 --> 00:33:28.193
She could be running west.
She could return.

492
00:33:29.569 --> 00:33:31.696
She could be already facedown somewhere.

493
00:33:33.907 --> 00:33:35.659
I just want to be free of her.

494
00:33:37.202 --> 00:33:39.621
I suspect
we'll never be totally free of her.

495
00:33:40.580 --> 00:33:41.957
Not even when she's dead.

496
00:33:46.586 --> 00:33:48.672
You're a great comfort. Tamacti Jun.

497
00:33:49.464 --> 00:33:53.843
If I relied on my charm.
I would have been finished ages ago.

498
00:34:07.148 --> 00:34:09.859
[Tormada] I want him gone. Immediately.

499
00:34:10.735 --> 00:34:12.946
And by gone. I mean dead.

500
00:34:13.029 --> 00:34:15.740
No. He will be an asset.

501
00:34:15.824 --> 00:34:18.034
If you don't have the stomach for it.
I'll do it myself.

502
00:34:18.118 --> 00:34:20.203
You will not.
I'm telling you. he can help us.

503
00:34:20.287 --> 00:34:22.414
- [Tormada] He is a liability.
- [Nevla] Enough.

504
00:34:22.497 --> 00:34:24.624
We cannot be arguing amongst ourselves.

505
00:34:25.667 --> 00:34:30.088
Need I remind you. if we do not succeed.
we will be hanged for insurrection.

506
00:34:30.171 --> 00:34:32.882
You speak as if
we were part of a petty coup.

507
00:34:34.009 --> 00:34:36.344
We assassinated two-thirds
of the Triangle.

508
00:34:36.428 --> 00:34:37.554
This is a coup.

509
00:34:38.054 --> 00:34:41.308
And for it to succeed.
we need to gain the trust of the people.

510
00:34:41.391 --> 00:34:44.853
The Payan queen's husband
will not inspire trust.

511
00:34:44.936 --> 00:34:47.063
He will do exactly that

512
00:34:47.147 --> 00:34:49.899
if Queen Maghra's own husband
has turned on her and joined us.

513
00:34:49.983 --> 00:34:54.070
Oh. you overestimate
your own appeal. Trovere.

514
00:34:54.863 --> 00:34:55.864
[scoffs]

515
00:34:55.947 --> 00:34:59.367
She would undo all of our hard work
because she fell in love with a Payan.

516
00:34:59.451 --> 00:35:01.828
Harlan is smart enough
to pick the winning side.

517
00:35:02.412 --> 00:35:04.039
He is intimately knowledgeable

518
00:35:04.122 --> 00:35:08.376
about every aspect of Pennsa's defenses
and mining operations.

519
00:35:09.586 --> 00:35:12.212
He will be an invaluable asset
to our new government.

520
00:35:13.965 --> 00:35:15.383
I am right about him.

521
00:35:15.467 --> 00:35:16.759
[Nevla] And if you're not?

522
00:35:18.344 --> 00:35:20.305
[inhales sharply] I'll kill him myself.

523
00:35:21.556 --> 00:35:24.808
Tormada rides out tomorrow.
You will accompany him.

524
00:35:26.603 --> 00:35:30.315
If you want to bring Harlan along.
then so be it.

525
00:35:30.815 --> 00:35:31.815
But. Trovere…

526
00:35:33.817 --> 00:35:36.154
this is no time to be sentimental.

527
00:35:41.201 --> 00:35:42.451
Hmm.

528
00:35:49.084 --> 00:35:52.545
[sighs. breathes heavily]

529
00:36:00.720 --> 00:36:02.472
[Kofun] How do you know Ranger?

530
00:36:02.555 --> 00:36:04.975
We grew up together. In Trivantes.

531
00:36:06.351 --> 00:36:07.560
Served together.

532
00:36:10.897 --> 00:36:15.402
After I killed my father.
it was Ranger who helped me escape.

533
00:36:17.570 --> 00:36:20.240
He gave me his own knots
to help me get past the gate.

534
00:36:21.950 --> 00:36:23.827
Edo found out and threw him in jail.

535
00:36:24.995 --> 00:36:26.663
[Kofun] You must have meant a lot to him.

536
00:36:26.746 --> 00:36:28.123
I owe him my life.

537
00:36:28.915 --> 00:36:31.042
So. why does he hate Tormada so much?

538
00:36:31.126 --> 00:36:33.587
Tormada used prisoners
for his experiments.

539
00:36:33.670 --> 00:36:35.880
[clicks tongue]
He believed he could restore sight.

540
00:36:36.881 --> 00:36:40.343
He never succeeded. but…
[sighs] …many suffered in his attempts.

541
00:36:41.803 --> 00:36:44.347
[Kofun] So that's why he has
the scars on his face?

542
00:36:44.431 --> 00:36:48.268
[Baba Voss] Tormada cut him open.
over and over again.

543
00:36:48.852 --> 00:36:50.061
Over many years.

544
00:36:51.896 --> 00:36:54.024
Tormada sounds like someone worth killing.

545
00:36:56.067 --> 00:36:59.404
Yes. Slowly.

546
00:37:01.489 --> 00:37:02.991
And many times over.

547
00:37:06.119 --> 00:37:09.623
[panting. grunting]

548
00:37:14.210 --> 00:37:15.211
Ah!

549
00:37:22.385 --> 00:37:23.929
Ah! Ah!

550
00:37:25.472 --> 00:37:28.224
Ah. ah! Ah!

551
00:37:28.808 --> 00:37:30.477
[yelping]

552
00:37:31.561 --> 00:37:33.188
[shouting]

553
00:37:38.777 --> 00:37:40.779
[moaning]

554
00:37:44.282 --> 00:37:46.993
[chuckling]

555
00:37:48.870 --> 00:37:52.123
[laughing]

556
00:37:57.295 --> 00:37:58.463
[sighs]

557
00:37:58.546 --> 00:38:01.341
[groans. sighs]

558
00:38:02.926 --> 00:38:05.053
[grunts. panting]

559
00:38:08.181 --> 00:38:10.684
[laughing]

560
00:38:21.820 --> 00:38:25.448
[rattling]

561
00:38:36.126 --> 00:38:38.753
[rattling continues]

562
00:38:41.047 --> 00:38:42.924
Oh. fuck.

563
00:38:43.967 --> 00:38:44.968
- [hisses]
- [screams]

564
00:38:45.051 --> 00:38:46.344
[grunting]

565
00:38:50.515 --> 00:38:53.476
[gasps. coughs]

566
00:38:53.560 --> 00:38:55.145
[inhales deeply. wails]

567
00:38:57.606 --> 00:38:58.815
[screams]

568
00:38:58.898 --> 00:39:02.110
[grunting. panting]

569
00:39:02.193 --> 00:39:03.278
[Sibeth] <i>Maghra.</i>

570
00:39:04.112 --> 00:39:06.156
[grunts. babbles]

571
00:39:06.239 --> 00:39:08.074
It won't work. Maghra!

572
00:39:08.158 --> 00:39:10.785
[Maghra grunting]

573
00:39:10.869 --> 00:39:12.954
I will not be put down like this.

574
00:39:13.747 --> 00:39:15.624
- [laughs]
- [panting]

575
00:39:16.416 --> 00:39:18.126
[grunting]

576
00:39:19.336 --> 00:39:20.337
I can hear you.

577
00:39:20.420 --> 00:39:23.214
I can hear you. you dumb bitch!

578
00:39:23.298 --> 00:39:25.508
[grunts. shouts]

579
00:39:25.592 --> 00:39:28.762
[panting]

580
00:39:28.845 --> 00:39:31.973
[laughing]

581
00:39:32.057 --> 00:39:34.100
[babbling]

582
00:39:34.184 --> 00:39:37.854
I... [laughing] Oh…

583
00:39:46.279 --> 00:39:49.074
[breathing heavily]

584
00:39:49.157 --> 00:39:52.118
[snake rattles]

585
00:40:08.635 --> 00:40:10.136
[rattling]

586
00:40:49.759 --> 00:40:50.969
Why did you stop?

587
00:40:51.553 --> 00:40:52.971
[Sheena] My mask keeps slipping.

588
00:40:53.972 --> 00:40:55.140
Then work without it.

589
00:40:58.143 --> 00:40:59.394
She can't.

590
00:41:00.478 --> 00:41:02.856
If she breathes in any of this.
it will burn her lungs.

591
00:41:02.939 --> 00:41:04.566
[guard] Stay at your station.

592
00:41:06.818 --> 00:41:08.820
I'll just fix her mask.

593
00:41:08.903 --> 00:41:11.072
[grunts. gasps]

594
00:41:11.656 --> 00:41:13.366
[guard] Finish your work.

595
00:41:14.993 --> 00:41:16.536
[grunting]

596
00:41:18.371 --> 00:41:20.332
- [guard] Lock her up!
- [Sheva panting]

597
00:41:20.415 --> 00:41:22.792
[guard 2] Go! You heard him.

598
00:41:24.002 --> 00:41:25.754
[guard 2] Walk! Hurry up.

599
00:41:30.050 --> 00:41:31.509
[whispering] What do you see?

600
00:41:32.135 --> 00:41:33.553
I don't see anything.

601
00:41:34.638 --> 00:41:39.225
- [Baba Voss] I don't sense any archers.
- [Haniwa sighs] There are no archers.

602
00:41:39.309 --> 00:41:40.852
[Baba Voss] No archers means what?

603
00:41:41.436 --> 00:41:45.774
[sighs] It means they are fortified
with more soldiers on the ground.

604
00:41:45.857 --> 00:41:46.900
Yes. my love.

605
00:41:47.567 --> 00:41:49.653
You and Wren. take Lu. go inside.

606
00:41:49.736 --> 00:41:51.571
Go find the children and bring them back.

607
00:41:51.655 --> 00:41:53.782
If they are sighted children.
that's where I belong.

608
00:41:54.282 --> 00:41:57.535
Fine. Gonna need a distraction.

609
00:42:01.581 --> 00:42:03.500
[fence rattling]

610
00:42:03.583 --> 00:42:05.001
- Form up.
- [guard 3] Sir.

611
00:42:05.085 --> 00:42:06.753
Someone's at the back fence.

612
00:42:10.215 --> 00:42:11.216
[groans]

613
00:42:15.011 --> 00:42:17.347
- You two. come with me.
- [guard 3] Yes. sir.

614
00:42:29.484 --> 00:42:31.027
[Charlotte clicking tongue]

615
00:42:42.330 --> 00:42:43.498
[grunts]

616
00:42:43.582 --> 00:42:45.375
- [grunting]
- [guard screams]

617
00:42:45.458 --> 00:42:46.626
[shouts]

618
00:42:46.710 --> 00:42:47.794
[guard groans]

619
00:42:47.877 --> 00:42:49.671
- [shouts]
- [groans]

620
00:43:01.308 --> 00:43:02.434
They're not here.

621
00:43:02.517 --> 00:43:04.269
Would they have been moved to Trivantes?

622
00:43:04.352 --> 00:43:07.314
No. This is where they build the bombs.
They need them here.

623
00:43:09.482 --> 00:43:10.650
Come on.

624
00:43:21.536 --> 00:43:23.163
[clatters]

625
00:43:23.246 --> 00:43:24.372
[guard] Pick it up.

626
00:43:26.958 --> 00:43:28.543
Now get back to work.

627
00:43:29.544 --> 00:43:31.087
[grunts. groans]

628
00:43:31.171 --> 00:43:32.881
[Lu straining]

629
00:43:33.465 --> 00:43:34.466
[shouts]

630
00:43:35.675 --> 00:43:36.760
[grunts]

631
00:43:37.761 --> 00:43:40.263
- [Lu shouting. straining]
- [guard 2 grunts]

632
00:43:40.347 --> 00:43:41.473
[shouts]

633
00:43:45.518 --> 00:43:47.896
[shouting]

634
00:43:48.563 --> 00:43:50.106
It's okay. You're safe.

635
00:43:51.358 --> 00:43:52.901
- [screams]
- [grunts]

636
00:43:52.984 --> 00:43:54.611
[guard groans]

637
00:43:54.694 --> 00:43:56.821
- [Sheena] They took Sheva.
- [Haniwa] Where?

638
00:43:56.905 --> 00:44:00.283
The back of the dormitory.
They lock us there as punishment.

639
00:44:00.367 --> 00:44:01.701
[exhales deeply] Okay.

640
00:44:01.785 --> 00:44:04.871
Um. take them to the woods out back.
I'll find Sheva.

641
00:44:04.955 --> 00:44:06.539
[grunting]

642
00:44:07.374 --> 00:44:08.583
[guard screams]

643
00:44:12.629 --> 00:44:14.130
- [bone snaps]
- [guard 2 shouts]

644
00:44:14.214 --> 00:44:15.548
[Ranger grunts]

645
00:44:17.259 --> 00:44:19.719
[breathing heavily]

646
00:44:20.345 --> 00:44:21.638
[whispering] Sheva?

647
00:44:23.890 --> 00:44:24.933
Sheva?

648
00:44:26.518 --> 00:44:27.519
Sheva.

649
00:44:30.730 --> 00:44:31.731
[Sheva] Haniwa?

650
00:44:31.815 --> 00:44:34.234
[breathing heavily]

651
00:44:46.246 --> 00:44:48.582
[sniffs. breathing heavily]

652
00:44:48.665 --> 00:44:49.958
What are you doing here?

653
00:44:50.041 --> 00:44:52.502
[Haniwa] It's okay. I'm here to help.

654
00:44:52.586 --> 00:44:55.088
- I don't believe you.
- I don't have time to argue.

655
00:44:55.589 --> 00:44:57.215
We're here to destroy the bombs.

656
00:44:57.716 --> 00:45:01.094
We already got the other kids out.
Just tell me where the bombs are.

657
00:45:01.970 --> 00:45:04.097
- You know about the bombs?
- Sheva.

658
00:45:05.265 --> 00:45:07.350
They're in the storehouse
behind the main house.

659
00:45:07.434 --> 00:45:10.979
Okay. Um. head to the woods in the back.

660
00:45:11.062 --> 00:45:13.064
My friends have your brothers and sisters.

661
00:45:13.148 --> 00:45:14.691
They'll get them somewhere safe.

662
00:45:14.774 --> 00:45:16.318
Oloman won't know where to find us.

663
00:45:16.401 --> 00:45:19.154
[breathing shakily]

664
00:45:23.241 --> 00:45:24.659
Oloman is dead.

665
00:45:25.243 --> 00:45:26.244
What?

666
00:45:27.287 --> 00:45:28.330
How?

667
00:45:29.039 --> 00:45:30.957
[Haniwa] He was killed by the Trivantians.

668
00:45:34.669 --> 00:45:37.297
Sheva. We can't stay here. I'm sorry.

669
00:45:39.341 --> 00:45:40.342
Here.

670
00:45:43.887 --> 00:45:44.971
Come.

671
00:45:45.472 --> 00:45:47.933
[Kofun shouts. grunts]

672
00:45:49.476 --> 00:45:50.560
[groans]

673
00:45:51.478 --> 00:45:52.979
[both straining]

674
00:45:54.856 --> 00:45:56.650
- [strains. shouts]
- [bone snaps]

675
00:45:56.733 --> 00:45:58.485
[guard 2 shouting]

676
00:46:00.362 --> 00:46:01.947
[grunts. groans]

677
00:46:04.115 --> 00:46:05.450
[guard 3 screams. gurgles]

678
00:46:06.409 --> 00:46:07.702
[grunts]

679
00:46:07.786 --> 00:46:08.787
[groans]

680
00:46:09.287 --> 00:46:12.999
[grunts] They're down.

681
00:46:13.083 --> 00:46:14.751
- Who is that?
- She's with us.

682
00:46:14.834 --> 00:46:17.003
- [hoofbeats approaching]
- [Kofun breathing heavily]

683
00:46:17.671 --> 00:46:19.881
- [Kofun] Trivantians.
- [Baba Voss] How many?

684
00:46:19.965 --> 00:46:22.133
[breathing heavily] Too many.

685
00:46:22.217 --> 00:46:23.426
Everyone inside.

686
00:46:24.135 --> 00:46:25.345
Ranger.

687
00:46:27.639 --> 00:46:28.640
[Ranger] Okay.

688
00:46:37.023 --> 00:46:38.400
[soldier shouts]

689
00:46:40.318 --> 00:46:41.861
[panting] Harlan.

690
00:47:01.089 --> 00:47:03.091
[inhales deeply]

691
00:47:07.762 --> 00:47:08.762
Hmm.

692
00:47:30.452 --> 00:47:31.452
[grunts]

693
00:47:35.832 --> 00:47:37.542
Oh. [chuckles]

694
00:47:41.504 --> 00:47:43.798
[laughs]

695
00:47:44.716 --> 00:47:46.134
[rattles]

696
00:47:55.977 --> 00:47:57.771
[laughs]

697
00:47:59.981 --> 00:48:03.026
[laughing]

698
00:48:09.908 --> 00:48:11.701
[sniffs]

699
00:48:19.876 --> 00:48:20.961
[grunts]

700
00:48:23.296 --> 00:48:24.547
Mmm.

701
00:48:32.555 --> 00:48:34.015
[chuckles]

702
00:49:20.312 --> 00:49:22.939
We are facing a crisis
unlike any we have ever known.

703
00:49:23.565 --> 00:49:26.651
The Trivantians now have weapons
that can destroy entire cities.

704
00:49:26.735 --> 00:49:28.737
They're coming to Pennsa
to do exactly that.

705
00:49:28.820 --> 00:49:30.822
What do you mean. "entire cities"?

706
00:49:30.905 --> 00:49:32.866
They've built weapons of the ancestors.

707
00:49:33.408 --> 00:49:37.037
Weapons like thunder and fire.
capable of tearing up the earth itself.

708
00:49:37.120 --> 00:49:40.582
That's absurd. They're lying
to influence the terms of the treaty.

709
00:49:40.665 --> 00:49:41.905
[Maghra] I wish that were true.

710
00:49:41.958 --> 00:49:43.318
It makes more sense than believing

711
00:49:43.376 --> 00:49:46.463
they have this fantastical weapon
you speak of.

712
00:49:46.546 --> 00:49:48.632
Your Highness.
let us not be fooled by their lies...

713
00:49:48.715 --> 00:49:50.926
Please. Please.

714
00:49:52.969 --> 00:49:55.180
I don't blame you for not believing.

715
00:49:55.263 --> 00:49:56.556
It sounds impossible.

716
00:49:56.640 --> 00:49:59.184
And no one will be happier than me
if I am wrong.

717
00:49:59.976 --> 00:50:03.688
But it is my duty. and yours.
to protect the Payan people.

718
00:50:03.772 --> 00:50:07.943
And I have heard enough
to believe that we are in grave danger.

719
00:50:09.235 --> 00:50:10.320
So. as your queen.

720
00:50:10.403 --> 00:50:15.116
I am asking you to put aside your doubts
and do your duty.

721
00:50:19.079 --> 00:50:22.165
We've sent a group
to destroy these weapons

722
00:50:22.249 --> 00:50:24.167
before they can reach our city.

723
00:50:24.251 --> 00:50:26.086
But we must be prepared for the worst.

724
00:50:26.169 --> 00:50:27.879
We are going to be invaded.

725
00:50:28.380 --> 00:50:30.048
And if we have any hope of stopping them.

726
00:50:30.131 --> 00:50:34.761
we will need not just every soldier
but every woman and man who can fight.

727
00:50:37.973 --> 00:50:41.518
Lady Benik.
Will I have your personal guard?

728
00:50:46.106 --> 00:50:47.565
Of course. my queen.

729
00:50:47.649 --> 00:50:48.650
[Maghra] Lord Diego?

730
00:50:51.069 --> 00:50:53.738
We will all yield our entire staffs
to the fight.

731
00:50:54.698 --> 00:50:55.865
[Maghra] Lord Torrance?

732
00:50:56.533 --> 00:50:57.617
My queen.

733
00:50:58.827 --> 00:50:59.869
Tamacti Jun.

734
00:51:00.829 --> 00:51:02.747
We will need the Witchfinders as well.

735
00:51:03.331 --> 00:51:05.250
They must be convinced to join us.

736
00:51:05.333 --> 00:51:07.919
You executed three of them
just the other day.

737
00:51:08.003 --> 00:51:11.214
But I spared the rest.
We will have to try.

738
00:51:14.843 --> 00:51:18.346
[Lucien] Great and mighty God Flame.
warm us with your grace.

739
00:51:19.180 --> 00:51:22.642
Grant us the strength
in these troubled times

740
00:51:24.060 --> 00:51:27.230
to cling to our faith
and execute your will.

741
00:51:28.773 --> 00:51:30.483
Ever since Kanzua fell.

742
00:51:31.151 --> 00:51:33.778
it feels like
the Payan Kingdom has lost its way.

743
00:51:35.572 --> 00:51:38.325
The Payan citizens are counting on us
to hold the line.

744
00:51:38.825 --> 00:51:40.035
So that's what we will do.

745
00:51:40.535 --> 00:51:42.495
And I know. like you do…

746
00:51:44.497 --> 00:51:46.333
we're going to get bloody doing it.

747
00:51:46.833 --> 00:51:48.501
They've already hung some of us.

748
00:51:49.127 --> 00:51:51.046
and we may all swing
when this is through.

749
00:51:51.546 --> 00:51:56.885
But like you. I will die a holy death
before I live an unholy life.

750
00:51:56.968 --> 00:51:59.095
- Lucien.
- Not now. Shiloh.

751
00:51:59.179 --> 00:52:00.263
The queen is here.

752
00:52:12.567 --> 00:52:15.946
Queen Maghra. This is a surprise.

753
00:52:16.029 --> 00:52:17.656
Maghra is not your queen.

754
00:52:17.680 --> 00:52:19.680
